		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES carts/chips question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When it has a gap, does that signify that it has blobs, and not chips?</div>
<br />
<br />Yep, that's the case with Mario/Duckhunt carts.  Most of them are the blob kind though.
<br />
<br />What they've done is taken the bare chip, and instead of putting it in a plastic package (wired to pins), they wire the chip directly to the board.  Then they put a glob of epoxy on top to hold it down and protect it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


